{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019x5aUdGazAJYdCp7SsDjf8","type":"tool_result","content":"94-\n95-- **CLI completeness:** Every FR maps to a CLI command or subcommand. Zero markdown-as-implementation.\n96-- **Showboat verify pass rate:** `showboat verify` confirms outputs match on re-run. Target: >98%.\n97:- **Sustained autonomous run:** Agent works >4 hours without human intervention via vendored Ralph loop.\n98-- **Iteration cycles per story:** Average implement→verify→fix loops before AC pass. Target: <3.\n99-- **100% test coverage:** Enforced project-wide as a quality gate. No blind spots accumulate across stories.\n100-- **All 12 known gaps resolved:** Every issue from the v1 audit is addressed by a specific FR and implemented in the CLI.\n--\n124-\n125-[Omitted long context line]\n126-\n127:**Resolution:** Alex runs `codeharness status` — 5/5 stories verified, 100% test coverage, all Showboat proofs pass. He didn't open the browser once. The sprint took 4 hours of autonomous execution.\n128-\n129----\n130-\n--\n138-\n139-**Climax:** Alex reviews the plan, approves it. `codeharness bridge --epics ralph/onboarding-epic.md` converts to tasks. `codeharness run` picks them up. Story 1: write tests for `auth` module — 100% coverage, Showboat proof showing all tests pass. By story 5, project-wide coverage is 100%. Stories 6-8: architecture doc and AGENTS.md files generated and verified.\n140-\n141:**Resolution:** `codeharness status` shows: 100% coverage, 5/5 modules with AGENTS.md, ARCHITECTURE.md current. The project is fully harnessed. Future sprints maintain these standards — the harness won't let them degrade.\n142-\n143----\n144-\n--\n318-|-----------|-------------|--------------|\n319-| Harness setup | `codeharness init` | Stack detection, enforcement config, dependency install (including beads), Docker stack (if observability ON), OTLP instrumentation, BMAD install + patches, state file, plugin scaffold |\n320-| BMAD→beads bridge | `codeharness bridge` | Parse BMAD epics/stories, extract ACs, import as beads issues with type=story, link to story files, set priorities from sprint order |\n321:| Autonomous execution | `codeharness run` | Vendored Ralph loop reading from beads (`bd ready`), fresh context per iteration, circuit breaker, crash recovery, verification gates per story |\n322-| Verification pipeline | `codeharness verify` | Quality gates → real-world verification → Showboat proof → flag updates → `bd update` status |\n323-| Status reporting | `codeharness status` | Harness health, sprint progress (from beads), verification state, Docker stack state |\n324-| Brownfield onboarding | `codeharness onboard` | Codebase scan, coverage gap analysis, doc audit, findings created as beads issues, onboarding epic generation |\n--\n543-\n544-### Reliability\n545-\n546:- NFR16: If VictoriaMetrics stack crashes, the harness must detect and report it (not silently fail)\n547-- NFR17: If agent-browser is unavailable, the harness must fall back gracefully (skip UI verification with warning)\n548-- NFR18: Hook failures must produce clear error messages, not silent blocks\n549-- NFR19: State file (`.claude/codeharness.local.md`) must be recoverable if corrupted — recreate from detected config\n550-- NFR20: BMAD harness patches must be idempotent — applying patches twice produces the same result\n551:- NFR21: Ralph loop must recover from crash and resume from last completed story\n552-- NFR22: `codeharness init` must be idempotent — re-running preserves existing config and verification log\n553-- NFR23: Doc-gardener scan must complete within 60 seconds\n554-- NFR24: AGENTS.md files must not exceed 100 lines (progressive disclosure — details in referenced docs)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011eJ4iFzBFG7CSy7fE3qSCc","session_id":"8b4a1da7-9e18-4302-ad13-ce7f0aff0314","uuid":"8073e64f-100c-4e6c-8217-217a4fc1e3cb","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:43:46.797Z"}
