{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WgzAbXxE8xDYAhxXftLbE1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 5.1: Flow Execution — Sequential Steps\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the engine to execute flow steps sequentially,\n9\tso that tasks run in defined order with state checkpointed after each task.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a `workflow-engine.ts` module at `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`\n14\t   **When** inspected\n15\t   **Then** it exports an `executeWorkflow(config: EngineConfig): Promise<EngineResult>` function that orchestrates sequential flow execution\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** a resolved workflow with `flow: [implement, verify]` where `implement` has `scope: per-story` and `verify` has `scope: per-run`\n19\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n20\t   **Then** the `implement` task runs once for each story/issue in the sprint before the `verify` task runs\n21\t   **And** `verify` runs exactly once after all per-story tasks complete\n22\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n23\t\n24\t3. **Given** a sprint-status.yaml with stories `[\"3-1-foo\", \"3-2-bar\"]` both in backlog/ready-for-dev status\n25\t   **When** the engine executes a `per-story` task\n26\t   **Then** it dispatches the agent once for story `3-1-foo` and once for story `3-2-bar`, in order\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t4. **Given** the engine completes a task dispatch for a story\n30\t   **When** the dispatch returns a `DispatchResult`\n31\t   **Then** `writeWorkflowState()` is called with an updated state containing the new `TaskCheckpoint` (task_name, story_key, completed_at, session_id)\n32\t   **And** state is written to disk before the next task begins\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** sprint-status.yaml exists with story entries and issues.yaml exists with issue entries\n36\t   **When** `loadWorkItems()` is called\n37\t   **Then** it returns a combined, ordered list of work items (stories and issues) ready for execution\n38\t   **And** issues are included alongside stories — the engine does not distinguish between them\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** no `issues.yaml` file exists at the expected path\n42\t   **When** `loadWorkItems()` is called\n43\t   **Then** it returns only stories from sprint-status.yaml without error\n44\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n45\t\n46\t7. **Given** a `per-run` task (e.g., `verify`)\n47\t   **When** the engine processes it in the flow\n48\t   **Then** it dispatches the agent exactly once (not once per story)\n49\t   **And** records a single `TaskCheckpoint` with `story_key: \"__run__\"` or similar sentinel\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011eJ4iFzBFG7CSy7fE3qSCc","session_id":"8b4a1da7-9e18-4302-ad13-ce7f0aff0314","uuid":"bd9ea035-1531-443f-8bb8-666960e7018e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:44:10.433Z"}
