{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RL1K8ArV7Pe3b3p8vDkEdF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is the summary:\n\n## What was done\n\n**Story 5-3: Crash Recovery & Resume** -- all 7 tasks implemented and tested.\n\n### Changes to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`:\n- **Task 1:** Added `isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, storyKey)` -- linear scan of `tasks_completed`, matches on both fields (tuple match)\n- **Task 1 (extended):** Added `isLoopTaskCompleted(state, taskName, storyKey, iteration)` -- counts matching checkpoints vs iteration number, needed because loop blocks reuse the same (task, story) pairs across iterations\n- **Task 2:** Early exit at top of `executeWorkflow()` when `state.phase === 'completed'` -- returns `{success: true, tasksCompleted: 0, storiesProcessed: 0, errors: [], durationMs: 0}`\n- **Task 3:** Per-story dispatch loop calls `isTaskCompleted()` before `dispatchTask()`, skips with warn log\n- **Task 4:** Per-run dispatch calls `isTaskCompleted()` before `dispatchTask()`, skips with warn log\n- **Task 5:** Loop block uses `isLoopTaskCompleted()` for both per-story and per-run tasks; iteration increment is guarded (only advances when current iteration is fully done)\n- **Task 6:** Verified: `getDefaultWorkflowState()` returns empty `tasks_completed`, `isTaskCompleted()` returns false for all when empty, corrupted state falls through to defaults\n- Exported `PER_RUN_SENTINEL` for test access\n\n### Changes to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`:\n- **Task 7:** 20 new tests across 3 describe blocks (`isTaskCompleted`, `isLoopTaskCompleted`, `crash recovery & resume`)\n- All ACs covered: skip completed sequential, skip completed per-story, per-run skip, mid-story resume (3/5 done dispatches 2), skip-to-verify, loop resume from current iteration, iteration counter preserved, fresh start, completed early exit, tuple matching, corrupted state, memory proportionality\n\n### Test results:\n- 88/88 tests pass in workflow-engine.test.ts\n- 4012/4012 tests pass across entire suite (zero regressions)\n- Coverage: 95.66% statements, 97.32% lines, 100% functions, 89.13% branches\n\n### Story status: `review`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Architectural decision:** The story spec's `isTaskCompleted()` with (taskName, storyKey) tuple matching is insufficient for loop blocks, because the same (taskName, storyKey) pair recurs each iteration. Added `isLoopTaskCompleted()` that counts checkpoint occurrences and compares to iteration number. This is a deviation from the spec's single-function design but necessary for correctness.\n- **Uncovered lines (97.32%):** Lines ~520, 554, 563-564 are uncovered -- these are edge cases in the loop block's iteration advancement logic for specific crash timing scenarios. Not worth adding contrived tests for the marginal coverage gain.\n- **No `--force` / `--fresh` flags:** As noted in the story's anti-patterns, these belong to story 5-4.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 28\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 14, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 4\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `npx vitest run workflow-engine` first attempt with failures (~40 lines), `find ... *.test.ts` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 8 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 3 times at different offsets)\n- Redundant operations: vitest run on workflow-engine.test.ts executed 3 times (initial failure check, after fix, after adding new tests) -- all necessary for iterative development"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a10037c04baf14282 (use SendMessage with to: 'a10037c04baf14282' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65478\ntool_uses: 53\nduration_ms: 351360</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b4a1da7-9e18-4302-ad13-ce7f0aff0314","uuid":"ef49a62c-ddf7-40db-b866-6b65abcc5a2d","timestamp