{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GD3dd86R9DYmBSHRKfrVV3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 5-3-crash-recovery-resume.md\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 1 found (workflow-state.ts changed but not in original File List)\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 4 Medium, 2 Low\n\n**HIGH Issues (fixed):**\n1. **Error checkpoints treated as successful completions** — `recordErrorInState()` added checkpoints to `tasks_completed` without distinguishing them from success checkpoints. On resume, `isTaskCompleted()` and `isLoopTaskCompleted()` would match these error checkpoints and skip tasks that actually failed. Fixed by adding `error?: boolean` field to `TaskCheckpoint`, setting it in `recordErrorInState()`, and filtering error checkpoints in both completion-check functions.\n\n**MEDIUM Issues (fixed):**\n2. **Test for stale verdict clearing had wrong dispatch count** — The test \"clears stale verdict after non-halt per-run error\" expected 4 dispatches but the correct behavior (post-fix) is 5 dispatches since error checkpoints no longer count as completions, causing the loop to re-dispatch verify before advancing iterations. Updated test expectations.\n3. **Missing branch coverage: non-halt per-story error continue path in loop** — Line 554 uncovered. Added test \"loop block: non-halt per-story error continues to next story\".\n4. **Missing branch coverage: per-run loop task skip on resume** — Lines 563-564 uncovered. Added test \"loop block: skips completed per-run task on resume\" (though these lines are still partially uncovered due to how the loop flow works when iteration is fully done).\n5. **Missing branch coverage: missing agent in loop task** — Line 520 uncovered. Added test \"loop block: missing agent in loop task is skipped gracefully\".\n\n**LOW Issues (not fixed):**\n6. **`projectDir ?? process.cwd()` default path never tested** — Lines 293, 471, 667 have fallback to `process.cwd()` that is never exercised. Low risk since the pattern is trivial.\n7. **`lastVerdict` is null on resume, changing retry scope** — On resume into iteration 2+, `lastVerdict` starts null which means retry dispatches for ALL work items rather than only failed ones. This is a conservative fallback (safe but wasteful). Could be fixed by reconstructing `lastVerdict` from `evaluator_scores` in the loaded state.\n\n**Results after fixes:**\n- Tests: 95 passing (was 88), 0 regressions across 4019 total tests\n- Coverage: 96.75% statements, 90.32% branches, 100% functions, 98.47% lines\n- All 158 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Overall coverage: 96.71% (passes 90% target)\n- Story status: updated to `verifying`\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — error checkpoint filtering in `isTaskCompleted()`, `isLoopTaskCompleted()`, `recordErrorInState()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — `error?: boolean` field on `TaskCheckpoint`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — 7 new/updated tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-3-crash-recovery-resume.md` — status to `verifying`, File List updated\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: Error checkpoints being treated as successful completions — `isTaskCompleted()` and `isLoopTaskCompleted()` did not distinguish between success and error checkpoints, causing failed tasks to be permanently skipped on crash recovery resume. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Test expectation mismatch exposed by the HIGH fix — existing test counted wrong number of dispatches because it relied on the buggy behavior. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `projectDir ?? process.cwd()` fallback never tested — trivial null coalescing, not worth adding tests for\n- `lastVerdict` is null on resume, causing conservative (all-items) retry scope instead of scoped retry — safe but wasteful behavior, should be tracked as tech debt for a future story\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Lines 513-514 (missing task in loop block warn path) still uncovered — requires a test with a completely missing task key in the workflow tasks map within a loop, which is an unlikely edge case\n- Lines 563-564 (per-run loop task skip path) partially covered now but the specific warn() call still uncovered — the test hits the `allCurrentIterationDone` branch instead\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The crash recovery pattern (read-before-dispatch, write-after-dispatch) is sound and follows the architecture doc.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story advanced to `verifying`.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 13, Edit: 9, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~20 lines), coverage output with all files (~80 lines), `npx vitest run` with failures (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 16 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 8 times due to size limits requiring offset/limit pagination)\n- Redundant operations: Multiple coverage runs (3) were needed to verify progressive improvements; the test file required 8 partial reads due to the 10k token limit — could have been more efficient with targeted grep searches for specific test sections"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac9803c1ec92684da (use SendMessage with to: 'ac9803c1ec92684da' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 93483\ntool_uses: 60\nduration_ms: 410227</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b4a1da7-9e18-4302-ad13-ce7f0aff0314","uuid":"6320b8b3-e703-44ea-8d87-c7b45044f8db","timestamp":"2026-04-02T22:59:51.096Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-3-crash-recovery-re