{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012h8m1F7shMXXZ5azvQxt95","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 5.3: Crash Recovery & Resume\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want the engine to resume from last completed task after crash,\n11\tso that long-running executions don't lose progress and don't require restarting from scratch.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** `executeWorkflow()` is called and `workflow-state.yaml` contains `tasks_completed` entries from a previous run\n16\t   **When** the engine begins iterating through flow steps\n17\t   **Then** it skips any (taskName, storyKey) combination already present in `tasks_completed`\n18\t   **And** resumes execution from the first incomplete task\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** `workflow-state.yaml` shows 3 of 5 per-story dispatches completed for task `implement`\n22\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` resumes\n23\t   **Then** it dispatches `implement` only for the 2 remaining stories (not the 3 already completed)\n24\t   **And** does not re-dispatch completed stories\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** `workflow-state.yaml` shows all per-story tasks completed but the per-run `verify` task is not in `tasks_completed`\n28\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` resumes\n29\t   **Then** it skips all per-story dispatches and proceeds directly to the `verify` task\n30\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** `workflow-state.yaml` shows a loop block was mid-iteration (e.g., `iteration: 2`, loop tasks partially completed)\n33\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` resumes with `--resume` or default behavior\n34\t   **Then** the loop block resumes from the current iteration, skipping already-completed tasks within that iteration\n35\t   **And** the iteration counter is NOT reset to 0\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t5. **Given** `workflow-state.yaml` does not exist or has `phase: idle` (fresh start)\n39\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called\n40\t   **Then** it executes all tasks from the beginning with no skip logic applied\n41\t   **And** behavior is identical to current (pre-crash-recovery) implementation\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** `workflow-state.yaml` has `phase: completed`\n45\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` is called without an explicit `--force` or fresh-run signal\n46\t   **Then** it returns immediately with `success: true` and `tasksCompleted: 0`\n47\t   **And** does not re-execute any tasks\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t7. **Given** a task checkpoint in `tasks_completed` with `task_name: \"implement\"` and `story_key: \"3-1-foo\"`\n51\t   **When** the engine evaluates whether to dispatch `implement` for story `3-1-foo`\n52\t   **Then** it matches on the (task_name, story_key) tuple — both fields must match to skip\n53\t   **And** a checkpoint for `(\"implement\", \"3-1-foo\")` does NOT cause `(\"verify\", \"3-1-foo\")` to be skipped\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t8. **Given** the engine is running a 4+ hour execution with many task dispatches\n57\t   **When** observed over the full run duration\n58\t   **Then** memory usage does not grow unboundedly (no leaked closures, event listeners, or accumulated temporary data structures beyond state)\n59\t   **And** the `tasks_completed` array growth is proportional to actual task count only\n60\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n61\t\n62\t9. **Given** `workflow-state.yaml` is corrupted or has an invalid shape (e.g., `tasks_completed` is not an array)\n63\t   **When** `readWorkflowState()` is called during resume\n64\t   **Then** it returns default state (existing behavior from `workflow-state.ts`)\n65\t   **And** the engine starts a fresh run rather than crashing\n66\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n67\t\n68\t10. **Given** unit tests for crash recovery and resume logic\n69\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n70\t    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for resume-related code paths covering: skip completed sequential tasks, skip completed per-story tasks, resume mid-loop, fresh start with no state, completed run early exit, tuple matching (task_name + story_key), corrupted state fallback, and all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n71\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n72\t\n73\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 1: Add `isTaskCompleted()` helper to `workflow-engine.ts` (AC: #1, #7)\n76\t  - [x] Implement `isTaskCompleted(state: WorkflowState, taskName: string, storyKey: string): boolean`\n77\t  - [x] Match on `(task_name, story_key)` tuple — both fields must match\n78\t  - [x] Return `true` if any checkpoint in `state.tasks_completed` matches both fields\n79\t\n80\t- [x] Task 2: Add early exit for already-completed workflows (AC: #6)\n81\t  - [x] At the top of `executeWorkflow()`, after reading state, check if `state.phase === 'completed'`\n82\t  - [x] If completed, return `EngineResult` with `success: true`, `tasksCompleted: 0`, `storiesProcessed: 0`, `errors: []`, `durationMs: 0`\n83\t  - [x] Do not modify state or write to disk\n84\t\n85\t- [x] Task 3: Add skip logic for sequential per-story tasks (AC: #1, #2, #7)\n86\t  - [x] In the per-story dispatch loop inside `executeWorkflow()`, before calling `dispatchTask()`\n87\t  - [x] Call `isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, item.key)` — if true, skip dispatch and continue to next item\n88\t  - [x] Log a skip message via `warn()` for observability: `\"workflow-engine: skipping completed task {taskName} for {storyKey}\"`\n89\t\n90\t- [x] Task 4: Add skip logic for sequential per-run tasks (AC: #3)\n91\t  - [x] In the per-run dispatch branch of `executeWorkflow()`, before calling `dispatchTask()`\n92\t  - [x] Call `isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, PER_RUN_SENTINEL)` — if true, skip dispatch\n93\t  - [x] Log a skip message via `warn()`\n94\t\n95\t- [x] Task 5: Add skip logic inside `executeLoopBlock()` (AC: #4)\n96\t  - [x] Inside the loop task iteration, before dispatching each task\n97\t  - [x] For per-story tasks: skip items where `isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, item.key)` with current iteration context\n98\t  - [x] For per-run tasks: skip if `isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, PER_RUN_SENTINEL)` for the current iteration\n99\t  - [x] Ensure `state.iteration` is NOT reset — preserve from loaded state\n100\t  - [x] If all tasks in a loop pass are already completed, proceed to the next iteration or termination check\n101\t\n102\t- [x] Task 6: Ensure fresh start works unchanged (AC: #5, #9)\n103\t  - [x] Verify `getDefaultWorkflowState()` returns empty `tasks_completed: []`\n104\t  - [x] Verify `isTaskCompleted()` returns false for all tasks when `tasks_completed` is empty\n105\t  - [x] Verify corrupted state falls through to default (already handled by `readWorkflowState()`)\n106\t\n107\t- [x] Task 7: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n108\t  - [x] Test: sequential per-story task skipped when checkpoint exists\n109\t  - [x] Test: sequential per-story task NOT skipped when no checkpoint\n110\t  - [x] Test: per-run task skipped when checkpoint exists\n111\t  - [x] Test: resume mid-story (3 of 5 done, dispatches only remaining 2)\n112\t  - [x] Test: resume skips to per-run verify when all per-story tasks done\n113\t  - [x] Test: loop block resumes from current iteration, skipping completed tasks\n114\t  - [x] Test: loop iteration counter preserved (not reset to 0)\n115\t  - [x] Test: fresh start (no state) executes everything — no skips\n116\t  - [x] Test: `phase: completed` returns early with `tasksCompleted: 0`\n117\t  - [x] Test: tuple matching — `(\"implement\", \"3-1-foo\")` does NOT skip `(\"verify\", \"3-1-foo\")`\n118\t  - [x] Test: corrupted state triggers fresh start\n119\t  - [x] Test: all existing story 5-1 and 5-2 tests pass (regression check is implicit)\n120\t  - [x] Verify 80%+ coverage on resume-related code paths\n121\t\n122\t## Dev Notes\n123\t\n124\t### Module Design\n125\t\n126\tThis story modifies `workflow-engine.ts` — the same file from stories 5-1 and 5-2. The crash recovery logic is woven into the existing execution paths (sequential and loop). No new files are created; this is purely additive.\n127\t\n128\tThe key insight: `workflow-state.yaml` already persists `tasks_completed` after every dispatch (implemented in stories 5-1 and 5-2). This story adds the **read side** — checking those checkpoints before dispatching, and skipping tasks that are already recorded as complete.\n129\t\n130\t### Integration Points\n131\t\n132\t- `WorkflowState.tasks_completed` — the checkpoint array is already populated by `dispatchTaskWithResult()` (story 5-1)\n133\t- `WorkflowState.phase` — used for early exit detection (`completed`) and fresh start detection (`idle`)\n134\t- `WorkflowState.iteration` — must be preserved on resume, not reset to 0\n135\t- `readWorkflowState()` — already handles corrupted/missing files by returning defaults (story 1-3)\n136\t- `writeWorkflowState()` — already called after every dispatch (no changes needed)\n137\t\n138\t### Resume Algorithm\n139\t\n140\t```\n141\texecuteWorkflow(config):\n142\t  state = readWorkflowState(projectDir)\n143\t  \n144\t  # Early exit: already completed\n145\t  if state.phase === 'completed':\n146\t    return { success: true, tasksCompleted: 0, ... }\n147\t  \n148\t  # Set phase to executing (preserves existing started, iteration, tasks_completed)\n149\t  state = { ...state, phase: 'executing', started: state.started || now() }\n150\t  \n151\t  for step in flow:\n152\t    if isLoopBlock(step):\n153\t      # Loop resume: iteration is already set from loaded state\n154\t      # executeLoopBlock skips completed tasks within each iteration\n155\t      executeLoopBlock(step, state, config, workItems)\n156\t    else:\n157\t      taskName = step\n158\t      if task.scope === 'per-run':\n159\t        if isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, '__run__'): skip\n160\t        else: dispatchTask(...)\n161\t      else: # per-story\n162\t        for item in workItems:\n163\t          if isTaskCompleted(state, taskName, item.key): skip\n164\t          else: dispatchTask(...)\n165\t```\n166\t\n167\t### Loop Block Resume Considerations\n168\t\n169\tThe tricky part is loop block resume. The `iteration` field is already persisted. On resume:\n170\t\n171\t1. `executeLoopBlock()` reads `state.iteration` from the loaded state (e.g., 2)\n172\t2. It increments to 3 at the start of each new pass\n173\t3. Within a pass, it checks `isTaskCompleted()` for each (taskName, storyKey) pair\n174\t4. Completed tasks within the current iteration are skipped\n175\t5. Once all tasks in the pass are dispatched (or skipped), termination conditions are checked\n176\t\n177\t**Edge case:** If the crash happened mid-loop-pass (e.g., iteration 2, retry task done but verify not done), the engine must:\n178\t- NOT increment iteration again (it was already incremented at the start of pass 2)\n179\t- Skip the completed retry tasks\n180\t- Execute the incomplete verify task\n181\t\n182\tThis means `executeLoopBlock()` needs to check if it's resuming a partially-completed iteration vs starting a fresh one. The simplest approach: always check `isTaskCompleted()` before dispatch. If all tasks in the current iteration are already done, the loop naturally advances to the next iteration.\n183\t\n184\t**Important:** The iteration increment at the start of each loop pass must be guarded — only increment if the current iteration's tasks are not all already complete. Otherwise, a resume after a crash between iteration increment and first task dispatch would skip an iteration.\n185\t\n186\t### What NOT To Change\n187\t\n188\t- `dispatchTaskWithResult()` — already writes checkpoints; no modification needed\n189\t- `writeWorkflowState()` — already writes after every dispatch; no modification needed\n190\t- `readWorkflowState()` — already handles corrupted files; no modification needed\n191\t- `loadWorkItems()` — work item discovery is unrelated to crash recovery\n192\t- `parseVerdict()`, `buildRetryPrompt()`, `getFailedItems()` — loop internals are unchanged\n193\t\n194\t### Memory / Long-Running Considerations (AC #8)\n195\t\n196\tThe engine uses immutable state updates (`{ ...state, tasks_completed: [...state.tasks_completed, checkpoint] }`). This means each dispatch creates a new array copy. For a run with N dispatches, this is O(N^2) total allocations but O(N) live memory — old arrays are eligible for GC.\n197\t\n198\tFor a 4+ hour run with ~100 dispatches (realistic upper bound: 20 stories x 5 iterations), the `tasks_completed` array stays small. No special memory management is needed.\n199\t\n200\tThe `isTaskCompleted()` function does a linear scan of `tasks_completed` for each dispatch decision. With ~100 checkpoints max, this is negligible.\n201\t\n202\tNo event listeners are registered. No closures accumulate across iterations. The only growing data structure is `tasks_completed` in state, which is proportional to actual work done.\n203\t\n204\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n205\t\n206\t- **Do NOT clear `tasks_completed` on resume** — that defeats the purpose of crash recovery\n207\t- **Do NOT reset `iteration` to 0 on resume** — loop state must be preserved\n208\t- **Do NOT add a separate \"resume mode\" flag** — the presence of existing checkpoints IS the resume signal\n209\t- **Do NOT change the checkpoint recording in `dispatchTaskWithResult()`** — the write side is correct\n210\t- **Do NOT add file locking or atomic writes** — single-process, single-writer, YAML is sufficient\n211\t- **Do NOT implement `--force` or `--fresh` flags** — that's story 5-4 (CLI commands)\n212\t\n213\t### Testing Strategy\n214\t\n215\tSame mocking approach as stories 5-1 and 5-2. Tests pre-populate `WorkflowState.tasks_completed` with checkpoints, then verify that `executeWorkflow()` skips those tasks and dispatches only the remaining ones.\n216\t\n217\tKey mock patterns:\n218\t- `readWorkflowState` returns state with pre-populated `tasks_completed`\n219\t- `dispatchAgent` mock tracks which (taskName, storyKey) pairs were actually dispatched\n220\t- Assert dispatched set equals expected (total - completed)\n221\t\n222\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n223\t\n224\tFrom story 5-2:\n225\t- `executeLoopBlock()` increments `state.iteration` at the start of each loop pass\n226\t- `dispatchTaskWithResult()` returns `{ updatedState, output }` — used by both sequential and loop paths\n227\t- `parseVerdict()` is called after per-run tasks in loops — resume must not re-parse already-scored verdicts\n228\t- `evaluator_scores` are appended per iteration — on resume, scores from previous iterations are preserved\n229\t\n230\tFrom story 5-1:\n231\t- `dispatchTask()` delegates to `dispatchTaskWithResult()` which records checkpoints\n232\t- `PER_RUN_SENTINEL = '__run__'` is the story key for per-run tasks\n233\t- `HALT_ERROR_CODES` set determines which errors stop execution\n234\t- State is written to disk after every dispatch via `writeWorkflowState()`\n235\t\n236\tFrom architecture-v2.md:\n237\t- \"State writes: After EVERY task completion. Never batch. Never defer. Crash recovery guarantee.\"\n238\t- `workflow-state.ts` is responsible for crash recovery (NFR6-8)\n239\t- Write-after-task pattern is already implemented — this story adds the read-before-task pattern\n240\t\n241\t### References\n242\t\n243\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 5.3: Crash Recovery & Resume]\n244\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Cross-Cutting Concerns — crash recovery]\n245\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Process Patterns — state writes]\n246\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#NFR21 — Ralph loop must recover from crash]\n247\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — executeWorkflow(), executeLoopBlock(), dispatchTaskWithResult()]\n248\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — WorkflowState, TaskCheckpoint, readWorkflowState(), writeWorkflowState()]\n249\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks.md — predecessor story]\n250\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps.md — foundation story]\n251\t\n252\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n253\t## Verification Requirements\n254\t\n255\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/5-3-crash-recovery-resume-proof.md)\n256\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n257\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n258\t\n259\t## Documentation Requirements\n260\t\n261\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n262\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/5-3-crash-recovery-resume.md\n263\t\n264\t## Testing Requirements\n265\t\n266\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n267\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n268\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n269\t\n270\t## Dev Agent Record\n271\t\n272\t### Agent Model Used\n273\t\n274\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n275\t\n276\t### Debug Log References\n277\t\n278\tN/A\n279\t\n280\t### Completion Notes List\n281\t\n282\t- Added `isTaskCompleted()` for sequential task skip logic (tuple match on task_name + story_key)\n283\t- Added `isLoopTaskCompleted()` for loop-aware skip logic (counts checkpoint occurrences vs iteration number)\n284\t- Added early exit when `phase === 'completed'` returns immediately with zero work\n285\t- Sequential per-story and per-run tasks check `isTaskCompleted()` before dispatching\n286\t- Loop block tasks check `isLoopTaskCompleted()` before dispatching\n287\t- Loop iteration counter preserved on resume (not reset to 0)\n288\t- Loop iteration increment guarded: only advances when current iteration is fully complete\n289\t- 20 new tests covering all ACs; 88 total tests pass; 0 regressions across 4012 tests\n290\t- Coverage: 95.66% statements, 97.32% lines, 100% functions, 89.13% branches\n291\t\n292\t### File List\n293\t\n294\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — crash recovery skip logic, `isTaskCompleted()`, `isLoopTaskCompleted()`, early exit\n295\t- `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — added `error?: boolean` field to `TaskCheckpoint` interface\n296\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — 20 new crash recovery tests + 7 review-fix tests (95 total)\n297\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VaeQzcFkX19B1DxwS1u7TA","session_id":"8b4a1da7-9e18-4302-ad13-ce7f0aff0314","uuid":"836b985b-cd1d-4dc8-9fdd-27c9f13b73c6","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:00:26.090Z"}
