{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UhkBBfuw3roBGSHc1qEUZP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UXofyhvHgymxatw6uN6T1h","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/5-3-crash-recovery-resume-proof.md","content":"# Story 5-3: Crash Recovery & Resume — Verification Proof\n\nStory: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-3-crash-recovery-resume.md`\nVerification tier: test-provable\nDate: 2026-04-03\nVerifier: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n## Build & Test Summary\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS — ESM build success, DTS build success |\n| Unit tests (`vitest`) | PASS — 4019 passed, 0 failed (155 test files) |\n| BATS integration tests | 68 passed, 253 failed (pre-existing failures unrelated to this story — shell scripts missing from repo) |\n| Lint (`eslint src/`) | PASS — 0 errors, 50 warnings |\n| Coverage (overall) | 97.49% lines, 96.71% statements, 98.12% functions, 88.13% branches |\n| Coverage (`workflow-engine.ts`) | 98.47% lines, 96.75% statements, 100% functions, 90.32% branches |\n| Coverage (`workflow-state.ts`) | 100% lines, 86.36% statements, 100% functions, 80.76% branches |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC #1: Skip completed (taskName, storyKey) on resume\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Test:** `crash recovery & resume > skips completed sequential per-story task (AC #1)` — PASSED\n- **Code:** `isTaskCompleted()` exported at `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts:120`, checks `(task_name, story_key)` tuple match\n- **Skip log:** `warn(\"workflow-engine: skipping completed task ${taskName} for ${item.key}\")` at lines 530, 772\n\n### AC #2: Resume dispatches only remaining stories (3 of 5 done, runs 2)\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Test:** `crash recovery & resume > resumes mid-story: 3 of 5 done, dispatches only remaining 2 (AC #2)` — PASSED\n\n### AC #3: Skip all per-story, proceed to per-run verify\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Tests:**\n  - `crash recovery & resume > skips completed per-run task (AC #3)` — PASSED\n  - `crash recovery & resume > skips all per-story tasks and proceeds to per-run verify (AC #3)` — PASSED\n- **Code:** Per-run skip logic with `PER_RUN_SENTINEL` at lines 563, 744\n\n### AC #4: Loop block resumes from current iteration\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Tests:**\n  - `crash recovery & resume > loop block resumes from current iteration, skipping completed tasks (AC #4)` — PASSED\n  - `crash recovery & resume > loop iteration counter is preserved — not reset to 0 (AC #4)` — PASSED\n- **Code:** `isLoopTaskCompleted()` exported at `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts:139`\n\n### AC #5: Fresh start (no state) executes all tasks\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Tests:**\n  - `crash recovery & resume > fresh start (no state) executes everything — no skips (AC #5)` — PASSED\n  - `isTaskCompleted > returns false when tasks_completed is empty (AC #5)` — PASSED\n  - `crash recovery & resume > does NOT skip per-story task when no checkpoint exists (AC #5)` — PASSED\n\n### AC #6: phase: completed returns early\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Test:** `crash recovery & resume > phase: completed returns early with tasksCompleted: 0 (AC #6)` — PASSED\n- **Code:** Early exit check `if (state.phase === 'completed')` at `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts:676`\n\n### AC #7: Tuple matching — both fields must match\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Tests:**\n  - `crash recovery & resume > tuple matching: (\"implement\", \"3-1-foo\") does NOT skip (\"verify\", \"3-1-foo\") (AC #7)` — PASSED\n  - `isTaskCompleted > returns false when taskName matches but storyKey does not` — PASSED\n  - `isTaskCompleted > returns false when storyKey matches but taskName does not (AC #7)` — PASSED\n\n### AC #8: Memory usage bounded, tasks_completed proportional\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Test:** `crash recovery & resume > tasks_completed growth is proportional to actual task count only (AC #8)` — PASSED\n- **Design:** Immutable state updates with `{ ...state }` — old arrays eligible for GC. No event listeners, no accumulating closures.\n\n### AC #9: Corrupted state triggers fresh start\n**Result: PASS**\n- **Test:** `crash recovery & resume > corrupted state triggers fresh start (AC #9)` — PASSED\n- **Code:** `readWorkflowState()` already handles corrupted/missing files by returning defaults (verified in `workflow-state.test.ts > readWorkflowState > returns default state and warns on corrupted YAML`)\n\n### AC #10: Unit tests pass at 80%+ coverage\n**Result: PASS**\n- 95 tests in `workflow-engine.test.ts` (20+ crash recovery specific), all passing\n- Coverage: 98.47% lines, 100% functions, 90.32% branches — exceeds 80% target\n- Zero regressions: 4019 total vitest tests pass\n\n## Files Modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | `isTaskCompleted()`, `isLoopTaskCompleted()`, early exit, skip logic in sequential and loop paths |\n| `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` | Added `error?: boolean` to `TaskCheckpoint` interface |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` | 20+ new crash recovery tests |\n\n## Additional Evidence\n\n- **Error checkpoint handling:** Tests confirm error checkpoints (`error: true`) do NOT cause tasks to be skipped on resume — `error checkpoints do NOT cause task to be skipped on resume (error!=completion)` PASSED\n- **Per-run sentinel:** `PER_RUN_SENTINEL = '__run__'` exported at line 103, tested via `isTaskCompleted > returns true for per-run sentinel key`\n- **Loop-aware completion:** `isLoopTaskCompleted` counts checkpoint occurrences vs iteration number — 3 dedicated tests all pass\n\n## Verdict\n\n**ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":271,"cache_read_input_tokens":42007,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":271,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo